    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-06-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="214" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                <head>No. 159.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">West</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-06-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 13,
                                1882</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Acknowledging the receipt of your note of the 27th of March last,
                            communicating to me a copy of a dispatch which has been addressed by Her
                            Majesty’s ambassador at Constantinople to British consular officers,
                            defining the grounds on which they are authorized to grant protection to
                            American citizens, I beg to convey to you an expression of the pleasure
                            with which the President has learned of the generous action of Her
                            Majesty’s Government on behalf of American citizens in the Ottoman
                            Empire.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
